There once was a chicken of some renown,
Whose courage had reached its culmination crown;
He strutted across roads, rivers and streams,
And even dared to enter a robin's nest;
But alas, he forgot that a chicken must cluck,
So he blathered on in his strutting kick-up. Ain't it the truth, dear friends, that sometimes we blur,
When we're full of pride and our ego's all fur;
Just remember to keep your beak on the straight and narrow,
Or you too might end up with a little too much gall.
